<ext_description linkend="Incomplete_data_reference_mechanism_arm.Incomplete_reference_marking">
An <b>Incomplete_reference_marking</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Classification_assignment:arm:Classification_assignment_arm.Classification_assignment"/> that assigns a particular marking to instances of an entity type selected in the <express_ref linkend="Incomplete_data_reference_mechanism:arm:Incomplete_data_reference_mechanism_arm.idrm_marked_item"/> select type.
This marking specifies that each of these instances are partly transferred in the exchange structure.
<example>If applied to an instance of <express_ref linkend="File_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.Digital_file"/>, then this marking indicates that the external file that should be provided with the <express_ref linkend="File_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.Digital_file"/> in the transferred data package, is not provided. 
This prevents the need to for repeated transfers of a big file between partners when its content has not changed.
</example>
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Incomplete_data_reference_mechanism_arm.Incomplete_reference_marking.items">
	the set of
	<express_ref linkend="incomplete_data_reference_mechanism:arm:Incomplete_data_reference_mechanism_arm.idrm_marked_item"/>s
	an <b>Incomplete_reference_marking</b> can be assigned to.
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Incomplete_data_reference_mechanism_arm.Incomplete_reference_marking.wr:WR1">
The marking shall only be applied to instances of an entity type selected in the <express_ref linkend="Incomplete_data_reference_mechanism:arm:Incomplete_data_reference_mechanism_arm.idrm_marked_item"/> select type.
</ext_description>

